's agricultural sector and overall economic development. Through these diverse yet interconnected initiatives, the Government of Bihar aims to foster a sustainable, productive, and green future for the state and its inhabitants.", "input": "\nYou are a helpful assistant responsible for generating a comprehensive summary of the data provided below.\nGiven one or two entities, and a list of descriptions, all related to the same entity or group of entities.\nPlease concatenate all of these into a single, comprehensive description. Make sure to include information collected from all the descriptions.\nIf the provided descriptions are contradictory, please resolve the contradictions and provide a single, coherent summary.\nMake sure it is written in third person, and include the entity names so we have the full context.\n\n#######\n-Data-\nEntities: \"GOVERNMENT OF BIHAR\"\nDescription List: [\"Aims to achieve 17% green cover in the state by promoting afforestation and wood-based industries\", \"Government entity responsible for the policy under which financial assistance is provided to new and existing wood-based units\", \"Provides benefits/incentives under various policies/schemes for agricultural development\", \"State government responsible for planning and development in Bihar, including agriculture and farmers' welfare\", \"The Government of Bihar prepared a draft on the State Policy of Water in 2010, addressing critical issues in water and sanitation in the state\", \"The state government aiming to achieve 17% green cover in Bihar by promoting afforestation and an efficient, integrated wood-based industry>\", \"The state government promoting agricultural and livestock productivity through various initiatives, including organic farming, new technology, high-yield varieties, and micro-irrigation methods\", \"The state government responsible for creating and implementing the Bihar Preservation and Improvement of Animals Rules, 1960\", \"The state government responsi